# Fitness Programming

Guidelines for exercise prescription, periodization, recovery protocols, and injury prevention within a whole-person wellness framework.

## Programming Principles

- **Readiness before intensity** - Always check the daily readiness score before prescribing workout intensity; never program a hard session on a low-readiness day
- **Progressive overload with guardrails** - Increase training stress by no more than 10% week-over-week for volume or load; larger jumps invite injury
- **Minimum effective dose** - Prescribe the least amount of training that produces measurable progress; more is not always better
- **Movement quality before load** - Technique mastery at lighter loads precedes heavy loading; form breakdown under fatigue is a signal to stop the set
- **Recovery is part of the program** - Deload weeks, rest days, and active recovery sessions are planned and scheduled, not reactive

## Exercise Prescription Framework

| Parameter | Beginner (0-12 months) | Intermediate (1-3 years) | Advanced (3+ years) |
|-----------|----------------------|------------------------|-------------------|
| Weekly frequency | 2-3 full body sessions | 3-5 sessions (split) | 4-6 sessions (specialized split) |
| Intensity (RPE) | 5-6 / 10 | 6-8 / 10 | 7-10 / 10 (periodized) |
| Sets per muscle group per week | 6-10 | 10-16 | 14-22 |
| Rep ranges | 8-15 (technique focus) | 6-12 (hypertrophy) + 3-6 (strength) | Mixed (periodized phases) |
| Progression model | Add reps first, then load | Wave loading, double progression | Block periodization, conjugate methods |
| Deload frequency | Every 6-8 weeks | Every 4-6 weeks | Every 3-5 weeks |

## Readiness-Based Session Selection

| Readiness Score | Session Type | Volume Adjustment | Intensity Adjustment |
|----------------|-------------|-------------------|---------------------|
| 85-100 (Peak) | Heavy compounds, PR attempts, high-intensity intervals | 100% planned | 100% planned |
| 70-84 (Good) | Normal training session as programmed | 100% planned | 100% planned |
| 55-69 (Moderate) | Technique work, moderate loads, steady-state cardio | Reduce 20-30% | Reduce 10-20% |
| 40-54 (Low) | Active recovery, mobility, light cardio | Reduce 50-60% | Cap at RPE 5 |
| Below 40 (Rest) | Full rest day or gentle walk | No structured training | No structured training |

## Periodization Structure

```text
Mesocycle Rotation (typical annual plan)
├── Accumulation Block (3-5 weeks)
│   ├── Higher volume, moderate intensity
│   ├── Build work capacity and muscle
│   └── RPE 6-8 target
├── Intensification Block (3-4 weeks)
│   ├── Lower volume, higher intensity
│   ├── Build maximal strength
│   └── RPE 8-9 target
├── Realization/Peak Block (1-2 weeks)
│   ├── Low volume, high intensity
│   ├── Test or compete
│   └── RPE 9-10 on key lifts
├── Deload (1 week between each block)
│   ├── Volume at 40-60% of previous block
│   ├── Intensity at 70-80% of previous block
│   └── Focus: recovery, mobility, technique
└── Active Recovery Phase (1-2 weeks annually)
    ├── Unstructured movement and play
    ├── Address accumulated imbalances
    └── Mental refresh from structured training
```

